claim.claim-text:
A line light irradiation device characterized by comprising:
an integrally molded casing having a bottom wall part extending in a longitudinal direction and a pair of side wall parts extending upward from both sides in the longitudinal direction of the bottom wall part;
an LED substrate provided on the bottom wall part of the casing;
a rod-shaped lens provided above the LED substrate along the longitudinal direction inside the casing; and
a fixing mechanism for fixing the lens to the pair of side wall parts,
wherein the fixing mechanism comprises:
an upward surface provided along the longitudinal direction in an inner surface of each of the side wall parts;
a downward surface provided along the longitudinal direction in each side peripheral surface of the lens;
a concave groove provided along the longitudinal direction above the upward surface in the inner surface of each of the side wall parts; and
an elastic body detachably provided in the concave groove and fitting into the concave groove to be in contact with the side peripheral surface of the lens in a state that the downward surface is in contact with the upward surface to thereby press the downward surface to the upward surface.

The manufacturing method according to claim 8, wherein the jig main body is a main body roller which is rotatable about a rotation axis,

the guide part is a guide roller coaxially provided with the rotation axis of the main body roller;

by rolling the guide roller while contacting with the upper surface of the casing in a state that one side surface of the main body roller is along an inner side surface of the casing, a side peripheral end surface of the main body roller is in contact with the elastic body to thereby fit the elastic body into the concave groove.
